WHAT ARE YOU DOING ON VALENTINES DAY?
💛
That’s the day SWALLOWED comes out and I’m sooo excited to finally be able to share this “official” trailer for it.
💛
It might not be your traditional type of valentines day story but if you like your love stories dark and disturbing and dripping with body fluids then SWALLOWED might just be for you.
💛
It stars Cooper Koch (who isn’t currently on IG) and Jose Colon (aka @thelightingaintright ) and the incredible @jenamalone and @markpattonnoes2 
💛
You’ll be able to find it on digital and on demand February 14
💛
…and if you wanna hear more about the movie or the process of “birthing” a micro-budget queer horror indie into the world sign up for DIRTY LITTLE FRIDAYS in my bio.
💛
WARNING: dirty little fridays contain raunchy NSFW pinups of @all_the_dead_boys 
;)
💛

Have you met Dom? These pictures are from that first day I shot @thelightingaintright (aka Jose Colon) for @all_the_dead_boys and “DOM” was born.
🐛
After we shot, I went back to Maine and started writing SWALLOWED. 
🐛
I found myself writing about Dom and his best friend Benjamin - who was moving off to LA and leaving Dom behind in the small Maine town where they grew up.
🐛
Flash forward two years and SWALLOWED comes out FEB 14th!
🐛
I’m not gonna lie - it wasn’t always easy and it took a looong time to get here (though in filmmaking two years seems like overnight)
🐛
And seeing these pictures where it all started sure does make me smile…
🐛
#swallowedthemovie 
#notthoseotherswallowedhashtags

Valentine’s Day is right around the corner…
💛
The PERFECT day to unleash a twisted backwoods queer horror love story like SWALLOWED.
💛
It’s got drugs! It’s got bugs! It’s got Jena Malone and Mark Patton as small town criminals wrapped up in some VERY shady dealings.
💛
And you’ll be able to find it wherever you rent or buy movies;)
💛

7 DAYS…
🐛
Mark Patton & Cooper Koch in SWALLOWED
🐛
“SWALLOWED is a dirty, transgressive, and sexy queer horror film that shuns the straight gaze for an unabashedly gay one. It’s a film for those of us who see our queerness as beautifully monstrous, gross, cool, sexy and a little scary.”
@mb.mcandrews for @dreadcentral 
🐛
Available on demand wherever you rent or buy movies.
February 14
🐛
#SWALLOWEDMOVIE

I can still hardly believe I got queer horror legend Mark Patton to play Rich in SWALLOWED.
🐛
Seeing him in Nightmare on Elm Street 2 was life changing for me. It was the first time I saw someone “like me” in one of the horror movies I loved so much. And that’s no small thing for a queer kid growing up in rural Maine.
🐛
Getting to watch Mark bring Rich to life in that backwoods cabin was a (twisted) dream come true.
🐛
I wrote the part specifically for Mark - and he was everything I hoped for and more.
🐛
Taking SWALLOWED to so many festivals - it’s been amazing to see how much love the horror community has for this incredible man who means so much to so many of us.
🐛
You’ll be able to see @markpattonnoes2 as RICH in SWALLOWED starting on Valentines Day.
🐛
You’ve been warned…
🐛
#SWALLOWEDMOVIE

Happy (almost) Friday. Here’s @owenlindberg for ALL THE DEAD BOYS.
.
Anyone who knows me knows how much I love creating stories and images for ALL THE DEAD BOYS aka ATDB.
.
It’s very much a one man show (I do the makeup, the wardrobe, the styling the digi-teching, the post production and pretty much everything else that goes into ATDB.
.
But that’s part of what make it so fun.
.
I’m gonna start posting some more of it here.
(since my @all_the_dead_boys account was deleted by IG…;(
.
.
You can sign up to get my ATDB ‘newsletter’ Dirty Little Fridays  at the link in my bio. It’s a weekly dose of dead boys ( and whatever else is going on in my world like making / releasing films like SWALLOWED and THE PASSENGER (my next one, which comes out later this summer).
.
DIRTY LITTLE FRIDAYS isn’t for everyone.
.
Consider yourself warned…

I spent my teenage years buried in the pages of @fangoria magazine oggling the special effects makeup of masters like Tom Savini and Rick  Baker and Dick Smith and Rob Bottin.
.
Eventually I added British Vogue and The Face and i-D to my magazine mix. And when I was working in fashion I got to work with soooo many incredible makeup artists.
.
ALL THE DEAD BOYS sits somewhere in the middle aesthetically.
.
Perched at that precarious place where the beautiful and the horrific meet.
.
Here’s a horrifically beautiful (?) shot of @michaelhartney from our ATDB shoot last week.
.
HAPPY FRIDAY

Found a stash of old polaroids tucked away in a box.
.
For years I had a huge wall of them that was constantly changing and shifting. So many of these faces inspired stories and characters and I spent hours and hours casting them in unmade movies.
.
The stash I just found was from a project I wrote called CURFEW. (a sort of Fight Club meets Frankenstein meets The Hitcher type story set in the seedy Vegas outskirts)
.
Some of these models I went on to work with over and over.
.
Some I met just the one time.
.
Like this guy. Im not sure who this is (the dangers of not labelling your polaroids as soon as you take them) but I’ve always loved his face and he would’ve made a great underground pit fighter.
Did someone say trouble?

Today is the start of Pride. In honor of that @mb.mcandrews wrote about the New Queer Horror Wave over at @dreadcentral. She had some really nice things to say about my film SWALLOWED, as well as @theoutwaters - my favorite movie from last year.
🩵
“June is here and as the temperatures rise, companies are dusting off their pride flags to show solidarity for the queer community. “
🩵
“This year, Pride is marked with anger at a country that continues to fail its queer communities, especially trans and non-binary individuals who are simply seeking a quiet, normal existence.”
🩵
“In the face of that anger, I want to take a moment to highlight how, while horror has always been queer, we are living in an incredible time of challenging and disgusting queer art.”
🩵
“Right now, we’re so lucky to be living through a New Queer Horror wave that isn’t just about queer side characters and homoerotic subtext. It’s about portraying ALL sides of the queer experience, not just sanitizing it for easy consumption by cis straight audiences who are treated like delicate little bombs who are set off by just a whiff of gay sex.”
🩵
“Earlier this year, we had the triple threat of Kyle Edward Ball’s Skinamarink, Robbie Banfitch’s The Outwaters, and Carter Smith’s Swallowed.”
🩵
“Sure, Skinamarink and The Outwaters are not outwardly queer, but their respective directors still imbue these films with a queer sensibility.”
🩵
“Then, there’s Smith’s Swallowed which is a nasty, bug-filled queer horror masterpiece that isn’t interested in either sanitizing its story or exploiting its characters. Smith rides a fine line of graphic violence that makes his Maine Gothic horror all the more terrifying.”
🩵
Thank you @mb.mcandrews for shining a spotlight and Robbie and Kyle for your incredible films. Long live New Queer Horror!
🩵
🩵
🩵
Here’s a (partial) list of new queer horror to watch out for.
.
THE OUTWATERS
.
SKINAMARINK
.

T BLOCKERS.

Anything and everything by @hystericteeth aka Eric LaRocca

Helllooooo from @fantastic.fest 2023!
.
(This pic has zero to do with Fantastic Fest but oh well)
.
It’s so much fun to be back in (sweltering hot) Austin for a long weekend of the best in all things weird and horrific. I was here last year with SWALLOWED but this year I’m on the “‘horror jury” (I don’t think that’s supposed to be a secret or anything).
.
Nothing beats bouncing from theater to theater - from one horror movie to the next. Probably sounds awful to some of you but for me it’s 🩵🩵🩵🩵🩵
.
The next movie is starting…

What a great @fantastic.fest !
Saw sooo many films (and friends) in Austin over the last few days. .
.
The standout film for me was VERMINES aka INFESTED by @sebvanicek which is coming to @shudder at some point (and hopefully will get a theatrical release because it is FUN to see this one with a crowd!) We awarded both Best Picture and Best Director to INFESTED as the “horror jury” and considering this is the directors first feature I’m super excited to see what he does next!
.
These are the films I saw over the last 5 days.
.
RAGE
.
WHEN EVIL LURKS
.
SLEEP
.
THERE’S SOMETHING IN THE BARN
.
SUBURBAN TALE
.
THE DEEP DARK
.
YOU’LL NEVER FIND ME
.
SUITABLE FLESH
.
WAKE UP
.
(This pic really has nothing to do with Fantastic Fest other than the fact that Ben lives in Texas and drove over to Austin to hang out on the opening night of the festival!)

I miss the days of big old school castings where I’d spend hours meeting boys and girls from all over the world who’d come to NYC and somehow ended up in my apartment with me. They’d share their portfolio (if they had one) and we’d chat a bit and I’d take a few polaroids.
.
I’d end up working with some of them over and over (like baby @ryanschira here) and some I’d never see again.
.
I’ve never thrown a single one of these polaroids away - and so many of them commanded such a  prime space for me in my “creative journey” (whatever that means). These faces were the starting place of so many stories - both ones that got told and ones that never did. 
.
 The “top spot” for a polaroid was eye level center on the massive, constantly changing polaroid wall.
.
That’s where this pic of Ryan lived for years and years and years.
THIS ONE IS 🔥 @jonnyinkk for ALL THE DEAD BOYS
